</TABLE>
>]
	NYCUJEnAXa [label=<
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLBORDER="1" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="4">
  <TR><TD BGCOLOR="#add8ff" WIDTH="150"><B>Analysis</B></TD></TR>
  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">The Tax Court found in the case before<BR ALIGN='left'/>us, that the merger of the three<BR ALIGN='left'/>Stauffer corporations was motivated<BR ALIGN='left'/>solely by legitimate business purposes,<BR ALIGN='left'/>the consolidation of the operational<BR ALIGN='left'/>facilities. Indeed, no losses occurred<BR ALIGN='left'/>until after the reorganization. Hence,<BR ALIGN='left'/>we are not confronted with purposeful<BR ALIGN='left'/>tax avoidance executed in compliance<BR ALIGN='left'/>with the code provisions.</TD></TR>
